-- Adaro, Berau Coal, Energi Mega, Medco: Indonesia Equity Preview
-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 2012-02-03T02:12:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-03/adaro-berau-coal-energi-mega-medco-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have  unusual  moves in  Indonesian trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index  rose 1.3 percent to 4,016.90.  Coal producers: Indonesian coal production rose 34 percent
to 371 million metric tons in 2011 from 276 million tons the
previous year, Kontan reported, citing Edi Prasodjo, coal
director at the nation’s energy and mineral resources ministry.
 PT Bumi Resources (BUMI)  , Indonesia’s largest coal producer,
gained 1 percent to 2,600 rupiah and  PT Tambang Babubara Bukit
Asam (PTBA)  , a state-coal producer, climbed 0.3 percent to
20,250 rupiah.  Energy companies: Crude oil futures fell to a six-week low
yesterday, dropping 1.3 percent to $96.36 a barrel in  New York .
Oil was last at $96.41 a barrel.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC) 
, Indonesia’s biggest listed oil company, was unchanged
at 2,275 rupiah and  PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG)  , the
second-biggest, fell 1 percent to 198 rupiah.  PT Adaro Energy (ADRO)  : The company’s net income for
this year and 2011 cited by the media yesterday were misquoted.
The earnings results are still being audited and will be
published March 30, Adaro said in a statement to the stock
exchange. Adaro suggests shareholders “continue to consider
market consensus,” it said yesterday. Adaro, Indonesia’s
second-biggest coal producer, jumped 4.8 percent to 1,960
rupiah.  PT Berau Coal Energy (BRAU)  : The company plans to sell
$500 million of fixed-rate, five-year notes, which will be used
to refinance debt and fund its activities, Berau said in a
prospectus published in Investor Daily. The stock advanced 3.6
percent to 435 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
